#NOTES

include <stdio.h> : is a header file which has the necessary information to include the input/output related functions (e.g. printf)

int main(void) : <return_type> <function_name> (<arguments>)

		says to compiler that it is going to return an integer
		Return 0 tell os that the program execution is succesful
		void means no argurment will be passed to main function

printf() used to print both strings and variables while puts() function only print string

string : s sequence of characters terminated with a null character \n or \0

%d takes integer value as signed decimal integer (takes negative and positive values) it assume base 10
